<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Powerpak, Wavy Lines, LCD]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7248&amp;p=71181#p71181"><![CDATA[
From the width of the stripes, it's noise at about 1.3MHz... possibly from intermodulation? One possibility is it's between the CIC (4MHz) and the PPU (5.4MHz) clock... If you're willing, you could try disabling the CIC on the mainboard. Also, the PowerPak is known to be higher power than most other carts, so maybe it's causing oscillations on the power supply. But I don't know how to test that last bit without an oscilloscope.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Tue Dec 07, 2010 10:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
